<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-19T12:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-19T12:30:00-05:00" n="1589" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1589">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/77.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi><note n="153" xml:id="d1589fn153">Communicated to the German Ambassador June 20, 1914.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-19T10:30:00-07:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1914, 10.30 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Carranza says you may inform his excellency, the German Ambassador,
                                that General Obregon has received strict orders to give ample
                                protection to all foreigners and their property during and after the
                                coming attack on Guadalajara.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>